cc:Work.dc:title: George Washington Carver
cc:Work.dc:description: A simple drawing of George Washington Carver (1864-1943), an American scientist, botanist, educator, and inventor. \nCarver is known for his research into and promotion of alternative crops to cotton, such as peanuts, soybeans and sweet potatoes, which also aided nutrition for farm families in the southern portion of the United States.
